data.title: Larry the Cable Guy Biography
data.meta_description: Read all about Larry the Cable Guy with TV Guide's exclusive biography including their list of awards, celeb facts and more at TV Guide.
data.text:
Fast Facts

Grew up on a Nebraska pig farm

Father was a part-time preacher, school principal and guitar player for the Everly Brothers

Performed in his first comedy club in 1986, on a dare from friends

Worked in radio as a disc jockey in Missouri

Developed comedic characters, including Larry the Cable Guy, as a call-in guest on various radio stations across the U

S

His trademark "Git-R-Done" was ad-libbed as a sign off for Larry

Released his first comedy album, Lord, I Apologize, in 2001

Was part of the successful Blue Collar Comedy Tour with Jeff Foxworthy, Bill Engvall and Ron White

Voiced the truck Mater in Pixar's Cars

Formed the philanthropic Git-R-Done Foundation to aid individuals in need and raise money for medical research

In 2011, hosted his own TV show on the History Channel: Only in America with Larry the Cable Guy
